HEADWORD: Heteroscian
<hw>Het`er*os"cian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/
other + <?/ shadow: cf. F. <ets>h⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧roscien</ets>.]</ety>
<def>One who lives either north or south of the tropics, as contrasted
with one who lives on the other side of them; -- so called because at
noon the shadows always fall in opposite directions (the one northward,
the other southward).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heterosis</ent>⟦br⟧
